Molecular and total evidence analyses were performed under the parsimony criterion using direct optimization (
Wheeler, 1996
), as implemented in the program POY 4.1.1 (
Varón et al., 2010
), to calculate dynamic homologies. The search strategy used in POY 4 is as follows, in sequential order: 1000 random addition sequences, SPR+TBR keeping one tree per search, select all. All characters were equally weighted, with gap opening 0. To assess nodal support, jackknife values were calculated in POY 4 using 1000 replicates, 1 random taxon entry, SPR+TBR, and saving 10 trees per replicate.

